1	//axhob_operation
2	{rbtgo_director_divest}
3	
4	The
5	{rbtr_director}
6	divests the
7	{rbtr_director}
8	{giam_service_account}
9	for this depot.
10	The operation accepts no CLI parameters; the
11	{giam_service_account}
12	email is resolved at runtime by reading the role's installed
13	{rbrr_director_rbra_file}
14	and extracting the `client_email` field.
15	After the cloud DELETE, the production RBRA file is removed from disk to mirror cloud state and prevent stale-credential reuse.
16	
17	//axhos_step
18	. *Authenticate as
19	{rbtr_governor}*:
20	.. Execute
21	{rbtoe_governor_authenticate}
22	.. {rbbc_store}
23	`«GOVERNOR_TOKEN»` for subsequent API calls
24	
25	//axhos_step
26	. *Read Role RBRA and Extract Service Account Email*:
27	.. {rbbc_require}
28	the role's installed RBRA file exists at
29	{rbrr_director_rbra_file}
30	.. {rbbc_fatal}
31	if the file is missing: "Director RBRA file not found — director may not have been invested"
32	.. {rbbc_store}
33	`«SA_EMAIL»` from the `client_email` field of
34	{rbrr_director_rbra_file}
35	.. {rbbc_fatal}
36	if `client_email` is empty or absent: "Director RBRA file present but client_email field is missing or empty"
37	
38	//axhos_step
39	. *Divest Service Account*:
40	.. {rbbc_call}
41	link:https://cloud.google.com/iam/docs/reference/rest/v1/projects.serviceAccounts/delete[iam.projects.serviceAccounts.delete] with:
42	... method: `DELETE`
43	... endpoint: `https://iam.googleapis.com/v1/projects/«DEPOT_PROJECT_ID»/serviceAccounts/«SA_EMAIL»`
44	where `«DEPOT_PROJECT_ID»` is derived as `RBDC_DEPOT_PROJECT_ID` from `(RBRR_CLOUD_PREFIX, RBRR_DEPOT_MONIKER)`, consistent with
45	{rbtgi_depot_project}
46	... header: `Authorization: Bearer «GOVERNOR_TOKEN»`
47	.. {rbbc_require}
48	HTTP 200 response OR HTTP 404 (already divested)
49	.. {rbbc_warn}
50	if HTTP 404: "Service account not found (already divested)"
51	
52	//axhos_step
53	. *Remove Production RBRA File*:
54	.. {rbbc_require}
55	the preceding DELETE succeeded (HTTP 200 or 404 — cloud state is authoritative)
56	.. Execute
57	{rbtoe_rbra_remove}
58	for the role's RBRA file at
59	{rbrr_director_rbra_file}
60	.. {rbbc_fatal}
61	if the file cannot be removed: "Failed to remove director RBRA file — manual cleanup required"
62	.. NOTE: Removing the RBRA file mirrors cloud state locally and prevents any process from reusing a credential that no longer corresponds to an active
63	{giam_service_account}.
64	
65	//axhos_step
66	. *Display Result*:
67	.. {rbbc_show}
68	single-line success naming `«SA_EMAIL»` and confirming the
69	{rbtr_director}
70	{giam_service_account}
71	was divested, or a notice that it was already absent
72	
73	//axhoc_completion
74	Successful execution removes the
75	{rbtr_director}
76	{giam_service_account}
77	from
78	{rbtgi_depot_project}
79	and deletes the local RBRA credential file.
80	Cloud state and local credential state are left in agreement: no stale key file remains after a successful divest.
81	A 404 response from the cloud DELETE is accepted as success — the
82	{giam_service_account}
83	is absent either way, and the RBRA file is removed regardless.
84

